@Node "Program history" "ClipHistory.guide/Program history"

	@{u}@{b}Program history@{uu}@{ub}

@{b}Version 1.0:@{ub}
	Initial release.

@{b}Version 1.1:@{ub}
	Removed some debugging code.

	Added the @{b}SINGLECLICK@{ub} flag. If YES, a single click on an item is
	enough to paste it to the clipboard. Use shift/alt/ctrl to select an item
	without pasting (a doubleclick with any qualifier down will also paste). If
	set to NO, a single click with any qualifier down will also paste the item.

	Recompiled with DICE 3.0.

	German catalog added. Unfortunately I don't have the source for it.. :)

@{b}Version 2.0:@{ub}
	@{b}ARexx@{ub}-port with over 40 commands added.

	@{b}ClipHistory@{ub} is now residentable! It wasn't that easy... :) (try
	yourself with DICE, a couple of callback hooks and a patch! :)

	French catalog and installer script by Georges Goncalves included.

	Danish catalog by Kenneth Fribert included.

	German catalog source included.

	@{b}MagicWB@{ub} icon by Georges Concalves included.

	Added menu items to load/save/view/clear the current clipboard
	contents. You can also view an item in the history.

	Any font specified in the tooltypes needed to be in memory for
	@{b}ClipHistory@{ub} to find it. Now it will try to load it from disk if
	possible.

	If the screenfont or the font specified in the tooltypes didn't
	open, @{b}ClipHistory@{ub} will now use the system default font instead
	(rather than topaz/8).

	Added the following arguments: @{b}PORTNAME@{ub}, @{b}NEXTKEY@{ub}, @{b}PREVKEY@{ub},
	@{b}AUTOSELECT@{ub}, @{b}SHOWCLIP@{ub}, @{b}TEMPDIR@{ub}, @{b}FILETYPE@{ub}, and @{b}SAVEPATH@{ub}. See
	@{"Options" Link "Options"}.

	@{b}ClipHistory@{ub} will now always exit even if someone have overpatched
	the function @{b}ClipHistory@{ub} may patch. If the patch was overpatched,
	there will be a small memory loss.

	When doing a full check, and a match is found, then @{b}ClipHistory@{ub}
	will select the item that matched, so that the selected item
	reflects the current clipboard contents. In general, @{b}ClipHistory@{ub}
	will do its best to keep the selected item up to date. This
	includes deselecting any item if no item in the history matches the
	current clipboard contents (e.g. a paste was filtered out)

	@{b}ClipHistory@{ub} will now use the OS 3.0 wait pointer when needed.

	@{b}SysIHack@{ub} "support" added (i.e. it handles larger-than-normal
	window size gadgets properly).

	The window will now backfill with the current background color,
	rather than color 0.

	The "Settings/Create icons" menu item was not working, in that
	icons never got created. I had written a function to do it, but it
	wasn't used anywere! :)

	Non-FTXT clips are now shown in real bold (if possible).

	When deleting a single item, a new item will be selected, if
	possible.

@{b}Version 2.1:@{ub}
	The selected item wasn't always visible when the window opened.

	Removed @{b}Enforcer@{ub} hits when data was written to the clipboard and
	the window wasn't open.

@{b}Version 2.2:@{ub}
	When copying a non-text clip from the clipboard to a file, then
	@{b}ClipHistory@{ub} would read innocent memory, and generate an incorrect
	(and often a very large) file.

	More tweeking of the @{b}ARexx@{ub} code. Made it somewhat smaller, and
	changed some other code to be more tolerant (e.g., stem base names
	no longer require a '.' char at the end. If not present, it will be
	added).

	Made a few minor fixes to the example @{b}ARexx@{ub}-script.

	Added scaled menu glyphs (OS 3.0+ only), based on source code from
	@{b}term@{ub}.

        Date in About requester localized. :)

        The @{b}ReqTools@{ub} file requester didn't open in the right drawer.

@{b}Version 2.3:@{ub}
	@{b}ARexx@{ub}-commands that return information caused @{b}Enforcer@{ub} hits, if no
	@{i}STEM-@{ui}name was specified.

	Fixed another bug in the @{b}ARexx@{ub}-interface, that could cause
	incorrect returns. I'm not sure if it actually could happen with
	the current command set, but... ;)

	Recompiled with SAS/C 6.56. Shaved off a few KBs.

	Alt-Return can be used to show the current clip in the GUI.

	@{b}ClipHistory@{ub} didn't make items visible properly on pre-OS 3.0
	Amigas.

	The @{b}ARexx@{ub}-command @{b}PutText@{ub} didn't always return errors as it
	should.

	If @{b}MATCH@{ub} was specified, and a newly added clip was identical to
	the last, the last clip was either not activated, or it was
	deactivated. Now it is properly activated.

	Added some new options: @{b}CENTERMOUSE@{ub}, @{b}NORMALGLYPHS@{ub}, @{b}SCREENMENUFONT@{ub}.
	See @{"Options" Link "Options"} for more information.

	Added the @{b}STICKY@{ub} option to the Options @{"menu" Link "Menus"}.

	Stopped using @{b}TexInfo@{ub} for this manual. This means that the
	ASCII-version will no longer be included.

	Specifying @{b}PORTNAME=""@{ub} didn't stop @{b}ClipHistory@{ub} from creating an
	ARexx-port with the default name.

	NewIcons included. From various sources, with minor changes by me.

	Fixed some bugs in the cleanup code, that could cause problems if
	ClipHistory failed to start up properly.

	Cleaned up some code.

@EndNode
